The paper deals with the hardness of approximating Max-2-CSPs with cardinality constraints, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of the Unique Games Conjecture also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper involves graph theory and optimization, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper uses techniques from linear programming and semidefinite programming, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
